De Granvine certainly was a very large holder, and of the rest De Londres, Sully, and Umfmville held four sees each, the largest recorded holding⁴ The honour oi Coyty also, held by Turber- ville, was equally considerable, and Talavan was an important barony; but Le Soor held only one see.
